    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-05T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/10–552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WAM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d744fn1">This telegram was sent also to New Delhi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-05T13:00:00+05:00"
                            >October 5, 1952—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>537. <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> this a.m. told me <gloss
                        target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> High Comm in India; Mohd Ismail has reported to
                    the <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> substance of his conversation with
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName>. <gloss target="#t_FonMin1"
                        >FonMin</gloss> said he would like United States Govt to know that <gloss
                        target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> has not made legalistic approach to Kashmir
                    problem since adoption of UN resolution. He added <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> agrees with point of view presented by <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName> that it would not be useful for
                        <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> to engage in legalities and further that
                    it is most useful for <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> to press for
                    implementation of plebiscite. He said he cannot agree with Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BCB1">Bowles</persName>’ thinking that presence 30,000 Indian
                    troops hidden in the mountains of Kashmir would have no effect on the
                    plebiscite. <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> reminded me that the
                    Kasmiri are a timorous people and the mere fact of 30,000 troops adjacent to the
                    Vale would undoubtedly influence the outcome of the election. <gloss
                        target="#t_ref1">Ref</gloss> Delhi’s 49, Oct 2, ’52.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d744fn2">Same as telegram 1408, <ref target="#d743">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WAM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
